@node "Introduction" "Introduction"
@next "Requirements"
@prev "Main"
@{u}Introduction - What Is Cyclone?@{uu}

Cyclone is a fidonet compatible point mail editor & tosser. It enables your
computer to process e-mail messages transported via a fidonet type network
(FTN). It will handle all the basic tasks expected of an e-mail program such
as reading, replying to and storing mail. It also has many advanced features
that serve to make things easier when handling large amounts of mail, or
performing complex tasks.

Cyclone comes into action when 'Packets' of e-mail arrive in your computer. To
handle the transfer of packets to & from your Amiga you will need a Mailer
program. Cyclone is set-up to use Trapdoor, but it works just fine with other
programs like GMS and Gotcha.


@{u}What Is So Special About Cyclone?@{uu}

Cyclone is the most modern and friendly FTN mail editor currently available
for the Amiga. In contrast to the out of date and user hostile interfaces of
many older programs Cyclone uses the Magic User Interface (MUI) system to
present an intuitive icon-driven interface to the user.

In addition to this Cyclone provides an array of powerful features unmatched
by any other point program. These include :

 + Intuitive MUI-Based interface, with toolbar and floating windows
 + Powerful Multi-Network capabilities
 + Mail filtering and re-direction at import time
 + Ultra-quick import module
 + Extensive sorting, listing and search options
 + Thread Listing and Navigation
 + Context Sensitive Pop-Up Menus
 + ARexx port
 + Support for Multiple Tagline Files
 + Fully Multi-Boss Capable
 + Seperate 68020/030 and 68040/060 Optimised Binaries
 + Comprehensive On-Line Help
 + Support for Messages With Embedded AmigaGuide and FTX Colour Codes
 + System Clipboard Interface
 + Packet and File Backup at Import Time
 + Fully Compatible With Virtual Memory and Disk Compression Software

@{u}Shareware Limitations@{uu}

Creating Cyclone has taken over 2 years of hard work. To ensure that this work
can continue the program has been released under the concepts of shareware.
This evaluation copy of Cyclone has certain limitations that can be removed by
registering the software. These limits do not prevent the program from
functioning. The evaluation version limitations are:

@{b}* No Purge Function@{ub}

The purge function removes unwanted messages and waste data from the message
base (store). Without this function the program will consume larger amounts of
disk space & memory, and become slower as time goes by.

@{b}* The Nag Requester@{ub}

This is a small requester that pops up whenever you run Cyclone to remind you
that the program is unregistered. It can be closed after a short delay.

@{b}* No NukeList@{ub}

The Nukelist is an advanced feature that allows you to filter out mail that
you do not want to read.

@{b}* No ARexx Port@{ub}

The ARexx port will not function on the unregistered version.

@{b}* No Taglines@{ub}

The internal tagline handler is disabled.

@endnode

@node "Requirements" "Requirements"
@next "License"
@prev "Introduction"
@{u}System Requirements@{uu}

Cyclone requires :

* AmigaOS 3.0 or 3.1

* MUI version 3.6

* MCC_NList v0.47 or later

* A 68020 main processor 4Mb of Ram.

* A working FidoNet mailer program. Trapdoor and GMS are the best
  known, but Cyclone will work with others. Trapdoor is the default
  mailer.

* A 256-line (PAL:Hires) or better display

A 68030 CPU, 6Mb of Ram and MUI 3.8 are strongly recommended.


@endnode
