@node "tooltypes" "ToolTypes"
@next "FAQ"
@prev "menus"
@{u}ToolTypes@{uu}

Cyclone supports a number of tooltypes:

@{b} POPLIST= [ON/OFF] @{ub}

  Unless this is set to OFF Cyclone will pop up the area list window every
  time you load the program. Disabling the initial area list is useful if
  Cyclone is being loaded so that an ARexx script can be run, perhaps by
  a Cron program.


@{b} DEBUG= [ON/OFF] @{ub}

  Toggles debugging mode. With debug mode enabled Cyclone will open a CON
  window and display internal information while it works.


@{b} ICONBAR= [HORIZ/VERT] @{ub}

  Sets orientation of the toolbar. NOTE: If you are running Cyclone on a
  screen with a vertical height of less than 480 pixels and wish to use
  a vertical toolbar you MUST enable Virtual toolbar mode.


@{b} VIRTUAL= [ON/OFF] @{ub}

  Toggles virtual toolbar mode. This alows vertical toolbars to work on
  screens of less than 480 pixels in height.


@{b} INDEXING= [FAST/DEEP] @{ub}

  Controls the type of re-indexing operation performed after imports. FAST
  mode does a single-pass index that assumes the message base is totaly
  valid. DEEP mode performs a complete validation of the message base as
  well as an total re-index.

  FAST mode is the default. As DEEP mode is very much slower than FAST it
  should only be used when you suspect corruption in the message base, or
  when statistics listed on the arealist do not match reality.


@{b} ALBAR= [ON/OFF] @{ub}

  Toggles vertical devider bars in the area list window.


@{b} MLBAR= [ON/OFF] @{ub}

  Toggles vertical devider bars in the message list window.

@endnode


@node "FAQ" "FAQ"
@next "AREXX"
@prev "tooltypes"
@{u}Cyclone FAQ@{uu}


@{b}I've been using Cyclone for a while and I've noticed that it's getting rather
slow at reading messages.@{ub}

The M1 database engine used by Cyclone is particularly sensitive to disk
fragmentation. When your hard drive gets fragmented Cyclone will slow down
quite a bit. To speed things up perform a Purge operation on large mail areas
and then use a utility like ReOrg or AmiBack Tools to de-fragment the drive.

Also, if your drive is formatted using the Directory Cache (FFSDC) filesystem,
you may be able to improve performance by converting it to standard FFS using
ReOrg. Using a small software cache, like HyperCache or CacheX, can also speed
things up.

Using an alternative filesystem like PFS or AFS can also help


@{b}Why are certain gadgets shaded out?@{ub}

These functions are not available yet. Look out for future updates that will
enable these functions.


@{b}Instead of icons I just get blank squares at the bottom of the main window.@{ub}

These icons rely on the AmigaOS 3.x datatypes system. If you are using AmigaOS
2.0x/2.x or your datatype drivers are incorrectly installed then you will see
only black squares.


@{b}When will Cyclone get Internet capability, like Thor?@{ub}

Never. Cyclone is a dedicated FTN mail editor and will not ever support other
systems. However, Cyclone has support for e-mail gateways.


@{b}I've decided I don't like Cyclone. Can I sell my keyfile to a friend?@{ub}

No. Keyfiles are non-transferable.

@endnode

