@node "Arexx_Req" "ARexx Requester Commands"
@next "Arexx_Msg"
@prev "Arexx_General"

NAME
     popalist

PARAMETERS
     None

DESCRIPTION
     Opens the area list window. Returns the name of the selected area in
the RESULT variable.

RESULT CODES
     None

NOTES
     None
---
NAME
     requestnotify

PARAMETERS
     PROMPT/A,CENTER/S

DESCRIPTION
     Pops up an minimal requester that takes it's body text from the PROMPT
parameter. The CENTER switch is only provided for compatibility with Rexx
scripts written for Spot. Requesters provided by Cyclone always use centered
text.

RESULT CODES
     None

NOTES
     None
---
NAME
     progressopen

PARAMETERS
     TITLE/K/A,PROMPT/K

DESCRIPTION
     Opens a progress bar identical to the one Cyclone uses during purge
of re-index operations. The title of the window is specified in TITLE, and
the body text in PROMPT.

RESULT CODES
     None

NOTES
     Remember to use progessclose when you are finished with the bar. Also
note that you can only have one progress bar open at a time. See the
ArchiveArea.Rexx script for an example of this command in action.
---
NAME
     progressclose

PARAMETERS
     None

DESCRIPTION
     Closes the progress bar window.

RESULT CODES
     None

NOTES
     None
---
NAME
     progressupdate

PARAMETERS
     REQ/A,CURRENT/A,TOTAL/A,PROMPT/K

DESCRIPTION
     Updates the progress bar. The parameters mean:

     CURRENT  - the current position of the bar.
     TOTAL    - maximum number thr bar can go to.
     PROMPT   - body text.

     The REQ argument is provided for compatibility reasons only and
performs no useful function.

RESULT CODES
     None

NOTES
     None

@endnode


@node "Arexx_Msg" "ARexx Message Commands"
@next "Arexx_Misc"
@prev "Arexx_Req"
NAME
     getmsgnum

PARAMETERS
     None

DESCRIPTION
     Returns the number of the current message in RESULT.

RESULT CODES
     None

NOTES
     None
---
NAME
     moveto

PARAMETERS
     TO/A

DESCRIPTION
     Jumps to a specified message number.

RESULT CODES
     0 if successful, or 5 if message out of range.

NOTES
     None
---
NAME
     write

PARAMETERS
     TO/K,TOADDR/K,FROM/K,SUBJECT/K,ORIGIN/K,FILE/K,NOSIG/S,NOEDIT/S,NOGUI/S,
     NOINT/S,NOTAG/S

DESCRIPTION
     Creates a new message in the current area. A blank message is created
if you do not specify a file name. The TO, TOADDR, FROM and SUBJECT fields
provide control over the message header info. The other args have the
following effects:

     ORIGIN     -  Overrides the set origin line with one you specify.
     NOSIG      -  Don't append you sig to the message
     NOEDIT     -  Don't load the message into the text editor for editing.
     NOGUI      -  Write message without opening the header window.
     NOINT      -  Don't prefix the message with the write intro string.
     NOTAG      -  Supress taglines.

RESULT CODES
     None

NOTES
     See EchoStat.Rexx for an example of this command in action.
---
NAME
     saveascii

PARAMETERS
     TO/K,OVERWRITE/S,NOHEADER/S,NOKLUDGES/S,NOTEARLINE/S,NOORIGIN/S

DESCRIPTION
     Dumps the current message into a textfile. If the OVERWRITE switch
is specified any existing data will be overwriten, otherwise it will be
appended to the end of the existing file. Other switches are pretty much
self-explanatory.

RESULT CODES
     None

NOTES
     This command allocates two buffers the size of the message to be saved
so beware of using it on large messages when memory is running low.
---
NAME
     getareaname

PARAMETERS
     None

DESCRIPTION
     Returns name of current area in RESULT.

RESULT CODES
     None

NOTES
     None
---
